beer_brewer_name: Amerisports Brew Pub at Ameristar Casino
review_blob: For $2.50 while playing craps I cant complain.  Its much like Boulevards Pale Ale but a bit lighter flavor.  I was just happy to get something other than macroswill at a casino.
One drink and I poured it out.  I know it was new to the shelf because it wasnt there just 4 days before so it couldnt be that old but it was by far the skunkiest and nastiest beer Ive ever tried.

Had it on draft on 6/1/2005 in Babes Resteraunt.  It was the only thing worth mentioning there.  Deep clear brown color with Malty flavor and flat syrupy mouthfeel.  It wasnt horrible but didnt stand out.

My favorite beer in the whole world so far.  I first tried this in Bellingham, WA in a sampler with the red, white, and blue.  I saved the blue for last and it was definately the premium.  Must have a trappist glass so the head doesnt overwhelm you.

Koningshoeven 4pk.  - purchased in Norman at hob nob robs.  Fantastic nose pours dark red with tan bubbly head.  I used a Chimay glass which felt right.  The taste was right in line with many of the Belgian Trappist ales with a bit more chocolate/caramel maltiness.  Very nice.

Oconnels in Norman on tap

Looked like an english brown but was heavier on hops and lite on malt.  It was nutty but not as sweet as I expected
Pretty bland with a strange falvor I cant Identify.  Hmm I dont really like i much.
beer_name: Big Sky Scape Goat Pale Ale

review_blob: Draft in LaConner, WA - Deep violet with no head.  Tart sour taste with sweet berry finish.  Very very nice.  Its better than any Lambic Ive had.
What a monster head.  A good third of the bottle ended up on the counter before I got it in a glass.   Cloudy orange with ample lacing.  Hoppy bite flavor is nothing special, but good.
Very nice fruity nose, nice appearance but with no head.  Flavor was disappointingly bland.

Too strange for me.  The good:  Very nice color and mouthfeel very complex taste.  The bad: Unfortunately the complexity seems to be made from a large variety of crap.  Im guessing that the big spill bucket at the end of the bar tastes something like this.  The nose is worse than the taste.  Ive got 5 more so maybe one will be better.
beer_name: New Belgium Lips of Faith - Biere de Mars

review_blob: Malty golden pilsner.  Almost as good as the ubiquitous urquel but not quite.  Ill have it again
alcohol and stinky feet.  Im guessing from the reviews i got a skunky pack.  Ill rerate again.
Poured clear brown, with fizzy tan head.  nice malty flavor with more spice than usual.  Quite yummy and Ill look for it again.

beer_brewer_name: Yakima Brewing And Malting Co./Bert Grants Real Ales
review_blob:
Cost Cutter Grocers - Bellingham, WA
Overpowering orange nose and flavor.  Think orange juice beer.  Its really not bad just very atypical and somewhat artificial tasting.

11.2 oz bottle from Haggen Grocery in Bellingham
What a head!  Clear golden pilsner look.  I should have followed the label pouring directions.  Great fruity flavor with a  bit of alcohol back bite.  Very nice.

Konig Ludwig weiss 11.2oz bottle
- Haggen Grocery Bellingham, WA - 
Great Hef!
lightly cloudy golden with little white head.  No lacing.  Nice fruity aroma but powerfully citrus like many hefs.  Maybe banana with a little spice.  Ill look for more.

Ive heard alot about this beer but spending most of my life under Oklahomas strange beer laws Ive never had the opportunity.  I really didnt see anything special.  It seems like a standard amber/copper ale, very mild hops and malts, no flavors discernable.  It wasnt bad at all just very standard.

beer_brewer_name: Portland Brewing Company (Pyramid - North American Breweries)
review_blob: Pored pretty clear for a hef, kinda a light brown,  head bubbled up and flew away super fast.  Watery, soapy, acidic, not a good hef.  crap I have 5 more.

Bayside Cafe - Bellingham, Wa
Deep black fine brown bubblew with deep roasted malt flavor.  Creamy and smooth, no acidity or bitterness, just smooth and sweet
$7.00 for 20+ oz!, orange amber, filtered but slighty hazy, nice balance of hop and malt but nothing memorable.
Cloudy amber with full creamy tan head.  Nice  texture with a good amount of sweet malty finish
beer_name: Mac and Jacks African Amber Ale

review_blob: slight hazy colo with white frothy head.  Lacing aplenty. Bitter dry front end with a brief honey sweet finish.  Too dry for my liking

Anthonys - Belingham, WA
Tasted like a generic amber, decent beer but no special.  Mild hops and malt but a little watery

Anthonys - Bellingham, WA
Wow, creamy and sweet like a hef but ful of robust chocolate, roasted malt, caramel flavors.  Very filling like an oatmeal stout but easy to drink.

Draft at Anthonys in Bellingham, WA and from the bottle in the same week.  The draf tof course was much better.  Orange and cloudy but the bottle poured clear.  Nice thick and creamy off-white head from both.  Decent Hef.
So far my favorite from boundary bay.  Medium brown cloudy color.  thick creamy texture, malty sweet and complex, well balanced.
Black, tan head, lotsa lacing, lotsa flavors going on.  cchoclate, licorice, much more flora and splicy flavors than i usually see in stouts.  Ill try it again.
Orange, cloudy, quite hoppy with a complex spicy flavor.  i dont usually like ipas but this oneill have again.
One of the better ESBs but rather mild.  Light cloudy amber.  spicy with hints of fruit.
On the better side of ambers but rather generic.  Cloudy with no head a little hopiness but nothing memorable
Unfiltered wheat color, wasnt much flavor but far superior to most blonde ales.  Slightly sweet finish.
not much to go on.  It taste like a macro attempt at a stout but it really had no distinct flavor outside of burned malt.  it wasnt horrible by any mean just really plain.

Yet again I have to wonder why mcguires keeps there average offerings on the menu hen they have it within their means to make such quality seasonal brews.  The hefeweizen was smoothly cloudy with a white head.  Clean but not watery mouthfeel with a fruity and acidic taste.  Stronger hoppiiness than most wheats.  Great beer all around.  Second only to mcguires millinium belgian as far as their offerings go.
barely there, very corona lite like with little to no flavor, bubbly clear wheat colored, closer to water than most beer.
Slighlt better than the typical mexican beers.  Better than corona and dos equis lage.  Clear golden with little white head.  A little bit malty in a good way.
cloudy golden color with fine snowwhite head that disapated quickly.  A little lacing.  medium mouthfeel.  Pretty typical wheat falvor with a mildly sweet and bitter finish.

McGuires Irish Pub - Pcola, FL 
Clear golden effervescent, little to no white head, strong floral nose, overly acidic hoppiness with no other interesting flavor.  Glad this is just a seasonal, yuck.

Bottle-Mellow Mushroom Pizza 
Mobile, AL
I was expecting nothing from this typical looking mass produced lager but was pleasantly surprised that this lager actually had a bit of sweetness and depth of flavor.  Certainly not a great beer but it does  amuch better job of approaching a reasonable lager unlike American macros.

Can-poured in to a pint glass

Wonderful fine nitrogen widget induced tan super creamy head, black color, very fine lacing., nice creamy full body with toned down roasted malt flavor. tastes like a guiness but nothing all that special or different.

Mobile, AL
Ugh... Something is going on at Jims cause I was a regular weekly patron but ALL of there beer has developed a nasty tart undertone that overpowers any good taste.  I had two pints of the seasonal "weiner" vienna lager and had a hard time finishing them.  Very acidic, but not in the good hoppy way, deep red color, no head, and the flavor could stand through strange acidic overtone.

Watery not much flavor, the color is more of an amber than the typical wheat colored light beer.  It tastes muchlike a fountain drink imitatio nof a beer.  Slightly better than a bud or coors light but not much.

Red Star Tavern - Spanish Fort, AL
Rather typical clear golden color with no head.  Hoppy start with little to no malt finish. Watery.
UPDATED: APR 24, 2005

El chico - Mobile, AL Draft $.99 special
Ive been low carbin it lately and usually miller light is my choice (I havent found sam adams light on tap anywhere).  Its pretty sweet and watery.  Better than bud light but not by much.  I guess its less fealing, but definately not great tasting.  pale yellow, white fizz.  barely there flavor.
Very mild for a pale ale.  Mouthfeel was a bit thicker than expected but the flavor was way too shy.  Mild hops.  Cloudy  gold with small white head.  nothing to right home about

Mellow Mushroom - Atlanta, GA Draft
Delicious nutty brown nicely hopped with well balanced caramel sweet aftertaste.  Deep brown, clear, no head.  Watery muthfeel.  Newcastle with hops.

My first Lambic.  Very nice.  Light orange collor with four or five small trails of bubbles.  Looks like a cloudy champagne.  Thick frothy off-white head that stayed and stayed.  Fruity nose, fruity tart and smooth.  Delicious but at $5.50/bottle I doubt Ill frenquent this stuff.

Cloudy orange in color with little to no head.  Served cold in an trappist glass.  Great floral and citricy nose. mouthfeel was multilevel, certainly not thick, but the higher alcohol gave it more weight in the mouth.  Flavor was sweet and hoppy, with a great tangy finish.  By far the best from Mcguires and near the top of my list as most enjoyable beer.

Its no great beer but you can really only fairly compare it to other light beers, soooo  it has a mild hoppiness to it certainly no malts, very watery but it does remind me of beer which is more than I can say for the other macro lites
